Earlier on Monday, the Alemayehu Ejigu, head of Oromiya region’s police commission had put the number of those arrested at more than 70 people. NAIROBI - Ethiopian police have detained 200 people in connection with violence on the outskirts of the capital on Saturday that left 23 dead, state-affiliated Fana Broadcasting said on Monday. Earlier on Monday, the Alemayehu Ejigu, head of Oromiya region’s police commission had put the number of those arrested at more than 70 people.